---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | LagSync"
  description="LagSync is privacy-first: no data collection, settings stored locally, and no tracking or third-party sharing.">
  <main class="pt-32 pb-20 flex-grow">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-8 font-['Space_Mono'] uppercase tracking-tight">
        Privacy <span class="text-cyan-500">Policy</span>
      </h1>
      
      <div class="space-y-12 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed font-light">
        
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 font-['Space_Mono'] uppercase text-sm tracking-widest border-b border-white/10 pb-2">01. Overview</h2>
          <p>
            LagSync is built with a "Privacy First" philosophy. We believe that a utility tool for your browser should do exactly what it says—sync your audio—and nothing else. <strong>We do not collect, store, or sell your data.</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 font-['Space_Mono'] uppercase text-sm tracking-widest border-b border-white/10 pb-2">02. Data Collection</h2>
          <p>
            LagSync does not collect any Personal Identifiable Information (PII). We do not track your browsing history, we do not use cookies, and we do not have a backend server to receive your data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 font-['Space_Mono'] uppercase text-sm tracking-widest border-b border-white/10 pb-2">03. Permissions</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">To function, LagSync requires the following permissions:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li><code class="text-cyan-400">storage</code>: Used strictly to remember your delay presets and settings locally.</li>
            <li><code class="text-cyan-400">scripting / all_urls</code>: Used to inject the audio-hooking script into websites containing video players. We only interact with HTML5 media elements.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 font-['Space_Mono'] uppercase text-sm tracking-widest border-b border-white/10 pb-2">04. Local Storage</h2>
          <p>
            All configuration data (your custom offsets, toggles, and donation link settings) are stored within your browser's local storage. This data never leaves your device.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 font-['Space_Mono'] uppercase text-sm tracking-widest border-b border-white/10 pb-2">05. Third Parties</h2>
          <p>
            Since we do not collect any data, no data is shared with third parties. If you click a donation link provided within the extension (e.g., Ko-fi or PayPal), you will be subject to that specific platform's privacy policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <div class="pt-10 border-t border-white/5">
          <p class="text-xs font-['Space_Mono'] uppercase tracking-widest">Last Updated: March 2026</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-block mt-6 text-cyan-500 hover:text-cyan-400 font-bold transition-colors">
            &larr; Back to Home
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>